        "order": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_PPT_ch7_page_132_1",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Vectors whose inner product is zero are called orthogonal. The length or norm of a vector in V is defined by",
        "bbox": [
          0.056666666666666664,
          0.13066666666666665,
          0.9286666666666666,
          0.23644444444444446
        ],
        "order": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_PPT_ch7_page_132_2",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A vector of norm 1 is called a unit vector. From these axioms and from (2) one can derive the basic inequality",
        "bbox": [
          0.05733333333333333,
          0.3244444444444444,
          0.884,
          0.42844444444444446
        ],
        "order": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_PPT_ch7_page_132_3",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "From this follows",
        "bbox": [
          0.058,
          0.5173333333333333,
          0.322,
          0.5626666666666666
        ],
        "order": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_PPT_ch7_page_132_4",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "(Triangle inequality).",
        "bbox": [
          0.62,
          0.5893333333333334,
          0.918,
          0.6444444444444445
        ],
        "order": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_PPT_ch7_page_132_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A simple direct calculation gives",
        "bbox": [
